4760-2026-P6 Memory Management
Name: Rebecca Hanessian
Date: 5/10/2026
Environment: macOS (Unix style)
How to compile the project:
	Type 'make'
How to run the project:
	./oss [-h] [-n proc] [-s simul] [-t timelimitForChildren] 
	[-i fractionOfSecondToLaunchChildren] [-f logfile]
Example:
	./oss -n 7 -s 3 -t 5 -i 0.3 -f log.txt
Explanation: 
	-proc is the number of user processes to launch
	-simul is the number of processes that can run simultaneously
	-timeLimitForChildren is the maximum simulated time that should pass before child 
		process terminates (in seconds)
	-fractionOdSecondToLaunchChildren is the minimum interval between launching child 
		processes
	-logfile is the filename to write OSS output
	Default proc is 15, default simul is 7, default timeLimitForChildren is 5.7,
		default fractionOfSecondToLaunchChildren is 0.2, default logfile is 'logfile.txt'.
